cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.RO 

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for 3D object shape prediction from single-view images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new algorithm for predicting depth maps, which involves modifying the network and evaluating models in a specific way, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the advantages and disadvantages of different shape representations, which is related to computer graphics (cs.GR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper's focus on 3D object shape prediction suggests that it may also be relevant to robotics (cs.RO).
